Shoepeg Phenotypes

Timothy M. Beissinger

September 19, 2016

4 fields (populations) of shoepeg were grown in Columbia, MO summer 2016 as the first generation of a long-term selection experiment. In each field, 96 plants were randomly selected and tagged. Tissue from these 96 plants was collected for genotypying, and they were phenotyped for plant height, ear height, ear number, and tiller number. This script will explore the phenotypic data.

Part 1: set working directory and load phenotypic data.

setwd("/home/beissinger/Documents/Shoepeg/2016/Phenotypes/")

rollins <- read.table("Shoepeg_cycle0_Rollins1_2phenotype.txt",header=T,stringsAsFactors=F,sep="\t")
genetics <- read.table("Shoepeg_cycle0_Genetics1_2phenotype.txt",header=T,stringsAsFactors=F,sep="\t")

Part 2: reformat data into one matrix with one row per plant.

# first sort rows so traits are always in same order (not sure why this isn't palm default)
rollins <- rollins[order(rollins$Location, rollins$Measurment, rollins$Trait),]
genetics <- genetics[order(genetics$Location, genetics$Measurment, genetics$Trait),]

phenos <- data.frame(Plant=rep(NA,384), Loc = rep(NA,384), PlantHeight = rep(NA,384), EarHeight = rep(NA,384), EarNum = rep(NA,384), Tillers  = rep(NA,384))


phenos$Plant <- c(rollins$Measurment[seq(1,765,4)], genetics$Measurment[seq(1,765,4)]) #note typo in "measurment"
phenos$Loc <- c(rollins$Location[seq(1,765,4)], genetics$Location[seq(1,765,4)])

phenos$PlantHeight <- c(rollins$Trait.Value[seq(3,767,4)], genetics$Trait.Value[seq(3,767,4)])
phenos$EarHeight <- c(rollins$Trait.Value[seq(1,765,4)], genetics$Trait.Value[seq(1,765,4)])
phenos$EarNum <- c(rollins$Trait.Value[seq(2,766,4)], genetics$Trait.Value[seq(2,766,4)])
phenos$Tillers <- c(rollins$Trait.Value[seq(4,768,4)], genetics$Trait.Value[seq(4,768,4)])

Part III: make plots of each phenotype in each field.

Part IV: determine truncation selection points. (these are the plant height criteria that females will have to be above or below to be harvested)

quantile(phenos$PlantHeight[which(phenos$Loc == "Rollins1")],c(0.05, 0.95), na.rm=T)
##     5%    95% 
## 147.75 215.00
quantile(phenos$PlantHeight[which(phenos$Loc == "Rollins2")],c(0.05, 0.95), na.rm=T)
##     5%    95% 
## 152.25 210.00
quantile(phenos$PlantHeight[which(phenos$Loc == "Genetics1")],c(0.05, 0.95), na.rm=T)
##  5% 95% 
## 140 205
quantile(phenos$PlantHeight[which(phenos$Loc == "Genetics2")],c(0.05, 0.95), na.rm=T)
##  5% 95% 
## 160 220
#pdf("ExperimentalEvolutionTruncationPoints_2016.pdf")
par(mfrow=c(2,2))
#Plant height truncation
hist(phenos$PlantHeight[which(phenos$Loc == "Rollins1")], main="Rollins 1: Tall; \n Plant Heights > 215cm",xlab="Plant Height")
abline(v = quantile(phenos$PlantHeight[which(phenos$Loc == "Rollins1")],c(0.95), na.rm=T), col="red",lwd=3)
arrows(222,15,227,15,length=0.1,col="red",lwd=2)
hist(phenos$PlantHeight[which(phenos$Loc == "Rollins2")], main="Rollins 2: Short; \n Plant Heights < 152cm",xlab="Plant Height")
abline(v = quantile(phenos$PlantHeight[which(phenos$Loc == "Rollins2")],c(0.05), na.rm=T), col="red",lwd=3)
arrows(148,16,143,16,length=0.1,col="red",lwd=2)
hist(phenos$PlantHeight[which(phenos$Loc == "Genetics1")], main="Genetics 1:Short; \n Plant Heights < 140cm",xlab="Plant Height")
abline(v = quantile(phenos$PlantHeight[which(phenos$Loc == "Genetics1")],c(0.05), na.rm=T), col="red",lwd=3)
arrows(138,15,133,15,length=0.1,col="red",lwd=2)
hist(phenos$PlantHeight[which(phenos$Loc == "Genetics2")], main="Genetics 2: Tall; \n Plant Heights > 220cm",xlab="Plant Height")
